    <item>
      <title>14.07 The Curse Jar (1)</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-07-the-cursed-jar-1/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-07-the-cursed-jar-1/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 17 Nov 2024 03:02:40 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.07 The Curse Jar&amp;nbsp;(1)&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-06-dining-hall/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;With Chue leading the way, Maomao was brought to Jinshi’s palace, or so she had thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The carriage arrived at a warehouse near Jinshi’s palace. At the site, lit by bonfires, were Jinshi, Basen, and Mamei. There were other guards she recognised, but as always, she didn’t remember their names, so let’s leave them out.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sorrry for being late at night.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was warmer than expected inside the warehouse. There was light as well as a few braziers. Although, she was uneasy about ventilation–Maomao made sure the windows and entranceway had been left ajar.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Pardon me for summoning you.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi was sitting on a simple chair, looking at a suspicious jar. It wasn’t the palace, but she could see the effort put into making this place as comfortable as possible. A space alike a small room had been built in the interior of the warehouse.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sorry for the abruptness, but can you take a look?” He glanced at Maomao, but shook his head lightly as if to tell himself that it wasn’t the time for this.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What an icky jar,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Don’t try to touch it while saying it’s filthy.” Jinshi slapped Maomao’s hand away.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If I do not touch it, we will not know what is inside.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We can leave that for someone else to do, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The jar was big enough to rest on two open palms. It was firmly sealed, with several talisman-like sheets pasted onto the lid. Curses had been written on the talisman, making it the very picture of a curse jar.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Suiren probably didn’t allow cursed items to be brought into the palace, which was why they were doing this in this warehouse.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What does it contain?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We have yet to investigate. It seems to be filled with a liquid. It shouldn’t be a poison derived from insects,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Well, it had been left long enough to liquify, that would be nasty.” Maomao had once neglected a snake she had been raising. At the time, it had dried up into a husk. “What if it contains blood?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao-san, you bring up unpleasant things to imagine, huuuh?” Chue was dramatically frightened.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So this was found at a high official’s house, right?” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah,” Jinshi replied.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“And it was brought to Jinshi-sama’s place.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao let out a huge breath.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It would be a different matter if it were the Eunuch Jinshi, but a personage had brought the curse jar to the imperial brother. No one would do such a bold thing. Normally, it would be perceived as disrespectful.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I have one person in mind who&lt;/em&gt;&amp;#8216;&lt;em&gt;d do such a thing.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But it wouldn’t be. The weirdo tactician was the first person that came to Maomao’s mind. That person would cook up something much different to harass Jinshi. Also, he would do it personally if it was an act that would harm himself. He wouldn’t need Jinshi’s help.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In that case…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She pondered through the process of elimination.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;Could it be related to the empress dowager’s family?” Although she had hesitated, she brought it up now.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi let out a big sigh instead of replying.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Also, with how clearly Basen was shaken, it had to be the case.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Word is that it was buried under the eaves. It was discovered by a cat they raised,” Jinshi said.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What a clever cat.” Maomao took out a towel from her breast pocket and wrapped her right hand in it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What are you planning to do?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You told me to investigate, but at this rate, we will not be able to do anything. How about I give it a feel for the time being?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But–”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi looked like he had a lot to say. Chue looked amused and Mamei held a towel out to Basen.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ll do it,” Basen said as he wrapped his hand in the towel. “My body is not so weak that it would lose to the likes of a curse.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, that’s true, but–”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Both Jinshi and Maomao looked uneasy. What should they do at a time like this? It seemed like some flag had been hoisted into the air.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Rather than Basen-sama, you should leave it to me,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, Maomao-san. My younger brother should be able to do this at least–”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A crack resounded without waiting for Mamei’s words.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A broken jar sat on Basen’s hand. He looked embarrassed. “With my hand wrapped up, I couldn’t control my strength…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You stupid younger brother!” Mamei’s humble expression transformed into that of a demon’s and she smashed a fist into Basen’s chin. The other guards wondered if they should stop her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Basen-sama is no good with fragile items, I see,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah. I knew that, I knew, but..” Jinshi was clutching his head too.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao crouched down and checked the smashed jar and the fluid that had spilled out.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Can Maomao-san see?” Chue brought the light closer for Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, that helps.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The contents were a dark fluid. It had a characteristic smell. It didn’t seem to be blood.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hey!” Jinshi stopped Maomao who had dipped her finger into the fluid. “What if you get cursed?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I will not get cursed. It is more annoying than a curse, though.” Maomao took a whiff of the fluid on her fingers. It smelt like tea. “As expected, poison. More correctly it would be poison in the middle of maturation.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was a strongly brewed tea.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-08-the-curse-jar-2/"&gt;Next chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-07-the-cursed-jar-1/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5040-6905976b86a9b' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20251101#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5040&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5040-6905976b86a9b' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5040-6905976b86a9b' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-07-the-cursed-jar-1/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/519581f02e9b429b5d35f4e877f50dbf.jpeg?w=200" type="image/jpeg"/>
